Stenoma pyramidea is a moth in the family Depressariidae. It was described by Lord Walsingham in 1913. It is found in Guatemala.The wingspan is 21â€“23 mm. The forewings are pale reddish fawn, shading to tawny on the dorsal half. A triangular pale reddish fawn dorsal patch beyond the middle, its apex reaching the lower margin of the cell. The hindwings are fawn grey.